The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, April 4: US-based Sherwin-Williams has purchased Nitco Paints for an undisclosed amount, the American firms vice-president Conway G. Ivy said here today. Nitco Paints has a manufacturing facility in Taloja, near Panvel, with a staff strength of 400 employees and has recorded sales of Rs 80 crore in 2006-07. Nitco Paints has a significant presence in the western region of the country. 

 New Delhi, April 4: The government has announced that it would extend limited service tax exemption to transport companies for the period April 1, 2000 to February 4, 2004. The finance ministry said service tax will be charged only on 40 per cent of the contract amount of tour operators for the said period.

 Mumbai, April 4: Sebi today banned 28 stock brokerages and eight individuals from trading in shares for five years for their role in the Ketan Parekh securities scam. 

 New Delhi, April 4: The government will announce the 3G spectrum policy by the end of this month, D.S. Mathur, secretary, department of telecom, said. The move will pave the way for mobile operators to offer voice, video and data services to subscribers.

 Mumbai, April 4: High inflation not only hurts the common man but also deters fresh investments, which are the key to faster economic expansion. Therefore, containing prices is an express requirement, the Reserve Bank said today.

 New Delhi, April 4: The shareholders of Hutchison Telecom will vote on a proposal to pay the Essar group $415 million to ensure smooth transaction with UKs Vodafone for sale of majority equity in Hutch Essar on May 8. 

 Mumbai, April 4: Fortis Healthcare plans to raise about Rs 504 crore from the capital market. Fortis has fixed the price band between Rs 92 and Rs 110 per equity share of Rs 10. The issue is open from April 16 to 20.




